pUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Let%20Young%20MPs%20Light%20Up%20This%20%26quot%3BDeep%2C%20Dark%20Chamber%26quot%3B%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EVery%20happy%20with%20the%20news%20that%20Swati%20Maliwal%2C%20the%20young%20firebrand%20chief%20of%20the%20Delhi%20Commission%20for%20Women%20(DCW)%2C%20has%20been%20nominated%20by%20the%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%20(AAP)%20as%20a%20candidate%20for%20election%20to%20Rajya%20Sabha.%20Maliwal%20(39)%2C%20when%20elected%2C%20will%20be%20part%20of%20a%20small%20group%20of%20young%20MPs%20in%20Rajya%20Sabha%20who%20are%20in%20their%2030s%20and%20early%2040s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20includes%20Jebi%20Mather%20from%20the%20Congress%2C%20AAP's%20Raghav%20Chadha%20(35)%2C%20and%20three%20of%20my%20colleagues%20from%20the%20Trinamool%20Congress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20is%20Saket%20Gokhale%20(36)%2C%20among%20India's%20foremost%20RTI%20activists%2C%20who%20has%20also%20faced%20incarceration%20for%20his%20activism.%20There's%20Prakash%20Chik%20Baraik%20(43)%20a%20popular%20and%20rising%20tribal%20leader%20from%20the%20Alipurduars%20who%20comes%20from%20a%20humble%20background%20of%20tea%20estate%20workers.%20More%20young%20blood.%20Meet%20Samirul%20Islam%20(36)%20an%20alumnus%20of%20IIT%20Delhi%20who%20spent%20a%20short%20while%20overseas%20and%20then%20gave%20it%20all%20up%20to%20come%20back%20to%20India%20and%20work%20at%20the%20grassroots%20for%20the%20welfare%20of%20the%20socially%20challenged%2C%20especially%20migrant%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20there's%20the%20plucky%20Jebi%20Mather%20of%20the%20Congress%20from%20Kerala%20who%20is%20an%20advocate%2C%20a%20former%20Municipal%20Councillor%20and%2C%20astonishingly%2C%20the%20first%20woman%20Rajya%20Sabha%20MP%20from%20Kerala%20in%20the%20last%2042%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20young%20colleagues%20of%20mine%20have%20entered%20Rajya%20Sabha%20with%20a%20great%20amount%20of%20hope%20and%20with%20the%20determination%20to%20excel%20in%20their%20responsibilities%20as%20parliamentarians.%20Whenever%20I%20chat%20with%20them%2C%20I%20am%20glad%20to%20see%20their%20enthusiasm%20and%20their%20faith%20in%20parliamentary%20procedure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet%20these%20young%20people%20do%20all%20it%20takes%20to%20light%20up%20an%20institution%20that%20is%20being%20turned%20into%20a%20deep%2C%20dark%20chamber.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20place%20for%20disagreements%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201987%2C%20the%20Chairman%20of%20Rajya%20Sabha%20emphasised%2C%20%26quot%3BEvery%20member%20is%20entitled%20to%20express%20his%20opinion.%20Merely%20because%20you%20disagree%2C%20you%20cannot%20shut%20him%20down.%20Then%2C%20there%20will%20be%20no%20parliament.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBetween%202019-2023%2C%20MPs%20faced%20suspension%20on%20multiple%20occasions%2C%20marking%20a%2013-fold%20increase%20from%20the%2015th%20Lok%20Sabha%20(2009-2014).%20Compare%20that%20to%20MPs%20from%20the%20ruling%20dispensation.%20Despite%20allegations%20of%20sexual%20harassment%2C%20use%20of%20toxic%20communal%20slurs%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20the%20House%2C%20and%20enabling%20a%20security%20breach%20in%20parliament%2C%20no%20action%20has%20been%20taken%20against%20any%20of%20them.%20No%20BJP%20MP%20has%20faced%20suspension%20in%20the%20last%2010%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQuality%20of%20Committees%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EParliamentary%20committees%20play%20a%20vital%20role%20by%20taking%20up%20crucial%20policy%20matters%20for%20discussion%2C%20inviting%20participation%20from%20stakeholders%20and%20domain%20experts.%20Consider%20this.%20The%20Home%20Affairs%20Committee%20while%20analysing%20the%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure%20(CrPC)%20Bill%2C%202006%2C%20which%20had%2041%20amendments%2C%20sat%20for%2011%20sittings.%20The%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%202023%2C%20one%20of%20the%20three%20Bills%20overhauling%20the%20entire%20criminal%20justice%20system%2C%20with%20356%20amendments%20(almost%20nine%20times%20that%20of%20the%20CrPC%20Bill)%20was%20discussed%20in%20just%2013%20sittings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBulldozing%20Legislation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20leader%20of%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20N.%20Gopalaswami%20Ayyangar%2C%20stressed%20in%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20that%20the%20purpose%20of%20a%20second%20chamber%20is%20to%20conduct%20dignified%20debates%2C%20delaying%20impulsive%20and%20hasty%20legislation.%20Significant%20Bills%20like%20the%201977%20Banking%20Service%20Commission%20Repeal%20Bill%20and%20the%202002%20Prevention%20of%20Terrorism%20Bill%20were%20passed%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20but%20rejected%20by%20Rajya%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20last%20winter%20session%2C%2047%25%20of%20Opposition%20MPs%20were%20suspended%20for%20demanding%20a%20discussion%20and%20statement%20from%20the%20Home%20Minister%20on%20the%20parliament%20security%20breach.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20the%20discussion%20on%20the%20Provisional%20Collection%20of%20Taxes%20Bill%20saw%20participation%20by%20just%20six%20members%20and%20was%20passed%20in%2030%20minutes.%20The%20Telecommunications%20Bill%20saw%20only%20eight%20members%20taking%20part%20in%20the%20discussion%20and%20was%20passed%20in%20an%20hour.%20The%20three%20critical%20Criminal%20Law%20Bills%20were%20passed%20in%20five%20hours%2C%20with%20the%20Home%20Minister%20himself%20speaking%20for%20an%20hour.%20Since%202019%2C%20over%20100%20Bills%20have%20been%20passed%20in%20less%20than%20two%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStealth%20and%20Secrecy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERule%2069%20of%20the%20Rules%20of%20Procedure%20and%20Conduct%20of%20Business%20in%20the%20Council%20of%20States%20(Rajya%20Sabha)%20states%20that%20a%20Bill%20should%20be%20circulated%20to%20MPs%20two%20days%20before%20it%20is%20taken%20up%20for%20consideration.%20Though%20the%20Chairman%20has%20discretionary%20power%2C%20this%20was%20a%20long%20established%20practice%20that%20had%20become%20convention.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20secrecy%20reigns%20supreme.%20Take%20the%20case%20of%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20Reorganisation%20Bill%2C%202019%2C%20which%20stripped%20J%26amp%3BK%20of%20its%20statehood.%20The%20Supplementary%20List%20of%20Business%20reached%20the%20members%20at%2011%3A18%20am%2C%20while%20the%20Bill%20was%20introduced%20at%2011%3A07%20am.%20It%20was%20discussed%20and%20passed%20on%20the%20very%20same%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENot%20House%20of%20Elders%2C%20but%20Council%20of%20States%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Council%20of%20States%2C%20unlike%20the%20House%20of%20Lords%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20was%20designed%20to%20genuinely%20deliberate%20and%20represent%20states%20and%20their%20interests.%20A%20notable%20instance%20of%20this%20occurred%20in%201989%20when%20Rajya%20Sabha%20rejected%20the%20Nagarpalika%20Bill%20passed%20by%20the%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20government.%20The%20Opposition%20in%20Rajya%20Sabha%20perceived%20it%20as%20a%20threat%20to%20the%20federal%20structure%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPost%202014%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20paradigm%20shift.%20The%20Opposition%20has%20been%20systematically%20targeted%2C%20from%20muting%20microphones%20and%20blacking%20out%20live%20feed%2C%20to%20outright%20suspension.%20The%20principles%20of%20federalism%20have%20been%20trampled%20upon.%20Bills%20aimed%20at%20weakening%20state%20governments%20such%20as%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20Reorganisation%20Bill%2C%202023%20and%20the%20Government%20of%20NCT%20of%20Delhi%20(Amendment)%20Bill%2C%202023%20were%20passed%20in%20less%20than%20half%20a%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20March%202016%2C%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20had%20stated%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20the%20Upper%20House.%20Whatever%20happens%20in%20this%20House%2C%20its%20impact%20is%20felt%20on%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20Assemblies%20and%20Municipal%20Corporations.%20So%20we%20should%20think%20how%20to%20create%20an%20atmosphere%20by%20which%20democracy%20can%20be%20strengthened.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResearch%20credit%3A%20Anagha%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Derek%20O'Brien%2C%20MP%2C%20leads%20the%20Trinamool%20Congress%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705039920000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-01%2Fvg9u2cs8_rajya-sabha-ani-1200_625x300_11_January_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Flet-young-mps-light-up-this-deep-dark-chamber-4840827%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22These%20young%20colleagues%20of%20mine%20have%20entered%20Rajya%20Sabha%20with%20a%20great%20amount%20of%20hope%20and%20with%20the%20determination%20to%20excel%20in%20their%20responsibilities%20as%20parliamentarians.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Flet-young-mps-light-up-this-deep-dark-chamber-4840827%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Except%20Yogi%20Adityanath%2C%20No%20Chief%20Minister%20Sent%20Invite%20For%20Ram%20Temple%20Event%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThousands%20of%20people%20from%20across%20the%20country%20are%20planning%20to%20attend%20the%20Ram%20Temple%20consecration%20ceremony%20in%20Ayodhya%20on%20January%2022.%20Families%20of%20Dalit%20icons%2C%20'karsevaks'%2C%20and%20several%20other%20prominent%20personalities%20have%20been%20invited%20to%20attend%20the%20mega%20ceremony.%20But%20the%20government%20has%20not%20sent%20invites%20to%20any%20Chief%20Minister%20except%20for%20Yogi%20Adityanath%2C%20sources%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BExcept%20for%20Yogi%20Adityanath%2C%20the%20chief%20minister%20of%20host%20state%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20no%20other%20chief%20minister%20has%20been%20invited%20for%20the%20%26quot%3BPran%20Pratishtha%26quot%3B%20(consecration%20ceremony)%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20source%20told%20NDTV.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20source%20also%20said%20that%20Union%20ministers%20and%20other%20top%20political%20leaders%20have%20not%20been%20%26quot%3Binvited%20for%20them%20being%20a%20minister%20in%20a%20state%20or%20the%20Centre%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFamily%20members%20of%20Dalit%20icons%20BR%20Ambedkar%2C%20Jagjivan%20Ram%2C%20Kanshi%20Ram%20are%20among%20those%20invited%20for%20the%20January%2022%20ceremony.%20Family%20members%20of%20%26quot%3Bkarsevaks%26quot%3B%2C%20who%20died%20during%20the%20Ram%20Janmabhoomi%20movement%2C%20have%20also%20been%20invited%20for%20the%20event%2C%20which%20will%20be%20attended%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThree%20retired%20chief%20justices%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20retired%20chiefs%20of%20all%20three%20services--%20army%2C%20navy%2C%20and%20air%20force%2C%20former%20ambassadors%2C%20top%20bureaucrats%2C%20IPS%20officers%20holding%20%26quot%3Bkey%20positions%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bbrothers%20and%20sisters%20honoured%20with%20the%20Nobel%20prize%26quot%3B%20are%20on%20the%20list%20invitees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20invites%20for%20the%20Ram%20Temple%20event%20have%20also%20snowballed%20into%20a%20political%20row%20with%20BJP%20slamming%20opposition%20parties%20like%20the%20Congress%20for%20skipping%20the%20ceremony.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECongress%20leaders%20Sonia%20Gandhi%2C%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge%2C%20and%20Adhir%20Ranjan%20Chowdhury%20have%20declined%20the%20invite%2C%20calling%20the%20event%20a%20%26quot%3Bpolitical%20project%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20BJP%20and%20its%20ideological%20mentor%20Rashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sangh%20(RSS)%20and%20asserting%20that%20%26quot%3Breligion%20is%20a%20personal%20matter%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Left%20and%20the%20Trinamool%20Congress%20have%20also%20declared%20they%20will%20forgo%20the%20ceremony.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP%20put%20out%20a%20%26quot%3Bname%20and%20shame%26quot%3B%20tweet%20blasting%20some%20of%20the%20opposition%20leaders%20with%20the%20caption%3A%20%26quot%3BNote%20the%20faces%20of%20Sanatan%20opponents%20who%20rejected%20the%20invite%20for%20the%20Ram%20Mandir%20ceremony%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705039620000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-01%2Fom304jvo_ayodhya-ram-mandir-idol_625x300_02_January_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fexcept-yogi-adityanath-no-chief-minister-sent-invite-for-ram-temple-event-sources-4847505%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Thousands%20of%20people%20from%20across%20the%20country%20are%20planning%20to%20attend%20the%20Ram%20Temple%20consecration%20ceremony%20in%20Ayodhya%20on%20January%2022.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fexcept-yogi-adityanath-no-chief-minister-sent-invite-for-ram-temple-event-sources-4847505%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fexcept-yogi-adityanath-no-chief-minister-sent-invite-for-ram-temple-event-sources-4847505%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fexcept-yogi-adityanath-no-chief-minister-sent-invite-for-ram-temple-event-sources-4847505%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India's%20Longest%20Sea%20Bridge%20Built%20With%20Quake-Resistant%20Tech%3A%20IIT%20Expert%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20historic%20Atal%20Setu%2C%20set%20to%20be%20inaugurated%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20in%20Mumbai%20today%2C%20will%20not%20only%20be%20India's%20longest%20sea%20bridge%20but%20also%20one%20of%20the%20strongest%20as%20it's%20been%20built%20with%20earthquake-resistant%20technology%2C%20an%20IIT%20Bombay%20expert%20told%20NDTV%20on%20Friday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2021%20kilometre-long%20bridge%20has%20been%20designed%20keeping%20in%20mind%20its%20location%20as%20Mumbai%20falls%20under%20a%20moderate%20earthquake%20damage%20risk%20zone%2C%20Professor%20Deepankar%20Choudhury%2C%20Head%20of%20Civil%20Engineering%20in%20IIT%20Bombay%20told%20NDTV.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-01%2F9td5b9vc_atal-setu-construction_625x300_12_January_24.jpeg%3Fim%3DFaceCrop%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSince%20a%20majority%20of%20the%20bridge%20is%20built%20over%20sea%2C%20we%20had%20to%20take%20into%20account%20the%20effect%20of%20seismic%20activity%20on%20the%20soil%20under%20it.%20It%20has%20been%20designed%20to%20withstand%20four%20different%20types%20of%20earthquakes%20of%20upto%206.5%20magnitude%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20team%20of%20over%20six%20IIT%20Bombay%20scholars%20worked%20on%20designing%20the%20bridge%20after%20the%20premier%20institute%20was%20roped%20in%20for%20the%20project%20in%202018.%20They%20submitted%20their%20report%20within%20six%20months%20detailing%20support%20systems%20to%20strengthen%20the%20foundation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-01%2Fjsqk8c8g_atal-setu-construction_625x300_12_January_24.jpeg%3Fim%3DFaceCrop%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20bridge%20to%20connect%20Mumbai%20and%20Navi%20Mumbai%20has%20been%20envisioned%20since%201963%2C%20so%20we%20are%20proud%20to%20be%20a%20part%20of%20this%20project%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Rs%2017%2C840%20crore%20bridge%2C%20also%20known%20as%20the%20Mumbai%20Trans%20Harbour%20Link%20(MTHL)%2C%20is%20set%20to%20cut%20the%20travel%20time%20be