%20by%20US%20and%20Ukrainian%20researchers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuch%20components%20are%20mostly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussias-microchips-search-hints-at-problem-for-us-chinese-militaries-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emicrochips%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20bearings%2C%20navigational%20systems%2C%20and%20other%20electronics%20that%20the%20Kremlin%20uses%20for%20its%20missiles%2C%20drones%2C%20and%20armored%20vehicles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20first%2010%20months%20of%202023%2C%20at%20least%2043.9%25%20of%20this%20imported%20tech%20was%20originally%20manufactured%20by%20companies%20headquartered%20in%20the%20US%20and%20its%20allied%20countries%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkse.ua%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2FChallenges-of-Export-Controls-Enforcement.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20joint%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20think-tank%20Yermak-McFaul%20International%20Working%20Group%20on%20Russian%20Sanctions%20and%20an%20analysis%20center%20at%20the%20Kyiv%20School%20of%20Economics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EManufacturers%20based%20in%20the%20US%20alone%20have%20contributed%20to%20at%20least%2027%25%20of%20the%20tech%20found%20in%20Russian%20weapons%20during%20that%20period%2C%20said%20the%20report%2C%20which%20advocated%20for%20the%20use%20of%20sanctions%20to%20pressure%20Russia%20away%20from%20its%20invasion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20total%2C%20the%20advanced%20tech%20imported%20by%20the%20Kremlin%20in%20those%20months%20is%20valued%20at%20%248.77%20billion%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESanctions%20have%20been%20working%20to%20some%20extent%2C%20the%20group%20said.%20Advanced%20electronics%20imported%20by%20Russia%20for%20military%20use%20declined%20by%2010%25%20since%20the%20war%20began%2C%20the%20researchers%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20much%20of%20this%20tech%20still%20originated%20from%20US-based%20companies%20like%20Intel%2C%20Advanced%20Micro%20Devices%2C%20and%20Texas%20Instruments%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20least%20%24351%20million%20worth%20of%20goods%20from%20Intel%20were%20imported%20for%20Russian%20weaponry%20from%20January%20to%20October%202023%2C%20while%20%24269%20million%20worth%20of%20tech%20came%20from%20Massachusetts-based%20Analog%20Devices%2C%20researchers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20%24174%20million%20of%20these%20goods%20were%20originally%20made%20by%20AMD%2C%20while%20another%20%24140%20million%20came%20from%20Texas%20Instruments%2C%20the%20research%20groups%20also%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EComponents%20from%20all%20of%20these%20companies%20have%20been%20found%20in%20Russian%20weapons%20retrieved%20from%20the%20battlefield%2C%20the%20report%20added.%20That's%20despite%20all%20of%20them%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fasia.nikkei.com%2FBusiness%2FTech%2FSemiconductors%2FSpecial-report-How-U.S.-made-chips-are-flowing-into-Russia%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehalting%20sales%20to%20Russia.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20clear%20that%20Russia%20continues%20to%20be%20able%20to%20acquire%20large%20amounts%20of%20goods%20that%20we%20consider%20to%20be%20of%20particular%20importance%20for%20its%20military%20industry%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20researchers%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20goods%20were%20largely%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-sending-russia-masses-of-military-gear-including-drones-report-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esold%20and%20dispatched%20through%20China%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Hong%20Kong%2C%20with%20nearly%2070%25%20arriving%20from%20these%20two%20regions%2C%20the%20group%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20also%20found%20that%20Chinese%20tech%20made%20up%2044.7%25%20of%20the%20imported%20components%20found%20in%20Russian%20weaponry%20during%20the%20first%20three%20quarters%20of%202023.%20That's%20more%20than%20the%20US%2C%20but%20still%20less%20than%20the%20amount%20of%20imported%20tech%20originating%20from%20the%20Western%20coalition%2C%20which%20includes%20South%20Korea%20and%20Japan%2C%20per%20the%20report's%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20also%20said%20its%20findings%20show%20it's%20highly%20likely%20Russia%20still%20needs%20Western%20advanced%20electronics%20for%20its%20weapons%2C%20meaning%20that%20export%20controls%20could%20still%20be%20effective%20in%20curbing%20Moscow's%20bombardments%20and%20drone%20strikes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20major%20changes%20to%20the%20current%20enforcement%20approach%20are%20needed%20to%20improve%20their%20effectiveness%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20called%20on%20Western%20lawmakers%20to%20step%20up%20restrictions%20on%20countries%20acting%20as%20third-party%20sellers%2C%20and%20to%20encourage%20the%20private%20sector%20to%20regulate%20itself%20better%20to%20comply%20with%20sanctions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20joint%20report%20comes%20just%20after%20Ukrainian%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskyy%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.president.gov.ua%2Fen%2Fnews%2Fusya-logistika-u-vijsku-maye-stati-shvidshoyu-zvernennya-pre-88169%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20on%20Tuesday%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Western%20sanctions%20were%20marred%20by%20loopholes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20clear%20evidence%20of%20a%20slowdown%20in%20the%20Russian%20defense%20industry%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20a%20video%20speech.%20%26quot%3BBut%20for%20the%20sanctions%20to%20be%20100%25%20effective%2C%20the%20schemes%20for%20circumventing%20the%20sanctions%20must%20also%20be%20100%25%20blocked.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Yermak-McFaul%20International%20Working%20Group%20on%20Russian%20Sanctions%20is%20partially%20run%20by%20Zelenskyy's%20office.%20Michael%20McFaul%2C%20former%20US%20ambassador%20to%20Russia%20and%20now%20a%20Stanford%20professor%2C%20also%20heads%20the%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhalf-russia-i