thers%20to%20%26quot%3Bsteer%20clear.%26quot%3B%20One%20woman%20claims%20that%20he%20ghosted%20her%20after%20they%20slept%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20Meta%20and%20the%20attorneys%20who%20filed%20the%20defamation%20case%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDaliah%20Saper%2C%20a%20principal%20attorney%20at%20Saper%20Law%20and%20defamation%20expert%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famber-heard-johnny-depp-settle-defamation-suit-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elegal%20cases%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20this%20are%20not%20uncommon.%20In%202022%2C%20a%20New%20York%20City%20woman%20received%20a%20cease-and-desist%20letter%20after%20she%20made%20a%20TikTok%20to%20warn%20other%20women%20about%20an%20unfaithful%20ex-boyfriend%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2022%2F07%2F18%2Ftech%2Fonline-whisper-networks-dating-safety%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECNN%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20are%20glaring%20missing%20pieces%20in%20the%20case%20involving%20the%2027%20women%2C%20Saper%20said%2C%20including%20how%20the%20lawsuit%20does%20not%20specify%20which%20statements%20are%20defamatory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20clearly%20know%20he's%20upset%20about%20what%20they%20posted%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20clear%20why%20it's%20defamatory%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20there's%20a%20lesson%20to%20be%20learned%20from%20the%20case%3A%20What%20you%20say%20online%20about%20a%20horrible%20date%20could%20wind%20up%20in%20a%20defamation%20lawsuit%2C%20regardless%20if%20you%20post%20it%20in%20a%20private%20Facebook%20group%20like%20%26quot%3BAre%20we%20Dating%20the%20Same%20Guy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20doesn't%20matter%20if%20the%20group%20is%20private%2C%26quot%3B%20Saper%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20just%20need%20to%20show%20a%20verbally%20false%20statement%20has%20been%20made%20about%20you%20and%20has%20been%20published%20to%20a%20third%20party.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20excludes%20opinions.%20Calling%20someone%20%26quot%3Bvery%20clingy%26quot%3B%20wouldn't%20be%20considered%20defamation%20but%20accusing%20someone%20of%20assault%20or%20drugging%20you%20would%20be%20examples%20of%20statements%20that%20could%20get%20someone%20in%20trouble%20if%20they%20can%20be%20proven%20to%20be%20false%2C%20Saper%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20four%20types%20of%20%26quot%3Bper%20se%20defamation%26quot%3B%20or%20written%20defamation%3A%20accusing%20someone%20of%20a%20crime%20such%20as%20sexual%20assault%3B%20accusing%20someone%20of%20having%20an%20infectious%20disease%3B%20accusing%20someone%20of%20conduct%20that%20would%20impact%20their%20job%3B%20and%20accusing%20someone%20of%20unchastity%20e.g.%20calling%20someone%20a%20%26quot%3Bwhore%2C%26quot%3B%20Saper%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAllegations%20of%20defamatory%20statements%20also%20need%20to%20outline%20what%20damages%20were%20incurred%20with%20each%20claim%20which%20Saper%20said%20was%20missing%20from%20the%20lawsuit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESaper's%20advice%3A%20%26quot%3BLimit%20the%20statements%20to%20verifiably%20true%20things.%20Anything%20that%20you%20can%20prove.%20Or%20anything%20that%20squarely%20can%20be%20construed%20as%20an%20opinion.%20'He's%20a%20jerk'%20is%20much%20different%20from%20saying%20'He%20roofied%20me.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20if%20you%20recently%20went%20on%20a%20bad%20date%20and%20feel%20compelled%20to%20shout%20about%20it%20into%20the%20digital%20atmosphere%2C%20you%20can%20%E2%80%94%20just%20be%20mindful%20of%20what%20you%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgossiping-social-media-defamation-are-we-dating-the-same-guy-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705016665000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.