he%20Department%20of%20Defense%20%26quot%3Bdid%20not%20maintain%20an%20accurate%20inventory%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20weapons%20designated%20for%20%26quot%3Benhanced%20end-use%20monitoring%26quot%3B%20(EEUM)%20that%20were%20delivered%20to%20Ukraine%20and%20%26quot%3Bdid%20not%20fully%20comply%26quot%3B%20with%20requirements%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Inspector%20General's%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ereport.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20unclear%20exactly%20how%20many%20weapons%20were%20considered%20delinquent%2C%20but%20the%20report%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bhigh%20rates%20of%20delinquency%20may%20correlate%20with%20an%20inability%20to%20maintain%20complete%20accountability%20of%20the%20EEUM-designating%20defense%20articles%2C%20which%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20may%20increase%20the%20risk%20of%20theft%20or%20diversion.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20beyond%20the%20scope%20of%20our%20evaluation%20to%20determine%20whether%20there%20has%20been%20diversion%20of%20such%20assistance%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20explained%20that%20getting%20a%20%26quot%3Bcomplete%20picture%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20EEUM-designated%20weapons%20in%20Ukraine%20%26quot%3Bwill%20be%20difficult%20as%20the%20inventory%20continues%20to%20change%2C%20and%20accuracy%20and%20completeness%20will%20likely%20only%20become%20more%20difficult%20over%20time%20as%20the%20total%20number%20of%20EEUM-designated%20defense%20articles%20in%20Ukraine%20continues%20to%20change.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fputin-orders-russia-troops-to-ukraine-major-escalation-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERussian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20launched%20his%20war%20against%20Ukraine%20in%20February%202022%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20US%20has%20given%20more%20than%20%2444%20billion%20in%20military%20assistance%20to%20Ukraine.%20The%20Defense%20Department%20inspector%20general's%20report%20comes%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5