ce%20for%20contempt%20to%20the%20magistrate%20also.%20Is%20this%20the%20manner%20in%20which%20they%20deal%20with%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20Order%3F%E2%80%9D%20asked%20Justice%20B.R.%20Gavai%2C%20another%20judge%20on%20the%20division%20Bench.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBusinessman%20Tusharbhai%20Rajnikantbhai%20Shah%2C%20a%20resident%20of%20Surat%2C%20has%20been%20accused%20in%20a%20cheating%20case.%20He%20was%20granted%20an%20interim%20anticipatory%20bail%20on%20December%208%2C%202023.%20According%20to%20Shah%2C%20he%20appeared%20before%20the%20police%20on%20December%2011%20to%20support%20the%20investigation%20but%20was%20arrested%20and%20released%20on%20bail%20the%20same%20day.%20The%20police%20then%20moved%20a%20remand%20application%20on%20December%2013%20before%20a%20local%20court%20resulting%20in%20his%20police%20custody%20for%20four%20days%2C%20Shah%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Mehta%20was%20livid%2C%20noting%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20very%20filing%20of%20the%20(remand)%20application%20was%20contempt%20on%20the%20face%20of%20it%E2%80%9D%20and%20called%20it%20%E2%80%9Cblatant%20illegal%20custody%20for%20four%20days!%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Gavai%20then%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9CLet%20the%20Magistrate%20and%20the%20IO%20be%20inside%20for%20four%20days.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20this%20juncture%2C%20additional%20solicitor%20general%20S.V.%20Raju%2C%20who%20appeared%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20Gujarat%20government%2C%20told%20the%20court%20that%20it%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Cblunder%E2%80%9D%20on%20the%20part%20of%20the%20investigating%20officer%20and%20tendered%20an%20apology.%20When%20the%20court%20sought%20a%20CCTV%20recording%20from%20the%20police%20station%2C%20Raju%20responded%20that%20it%20was%20not%20functional.%20To%20this%2C%20Justice%20Gavai%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20shows%20the%20conduct.%20On%20the%20very%20same%20day%2C%20it%20is%20not%20functioning!%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Mehta%20chimed%20in%2C%20by%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20was%20expected.%20It%E2%80%99s%20intentional%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D.%20He%20then%20went%20on%20to%20ask%2C%20%E2%80%9CIn%20a%20civil%20nature%20case%2C%20why%20remand%20is%20required%3F%20A%20murder%20weapon%20was%20to%20be%20recovered%20or%20what%3F%E2%80%9D.%20Justice%20Mehta%20specifically%20said%20the%20authorities%20must%20explain%20why%20CCTV%20was%20not%20functioning%20on%20the%20said%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20asked%20authorities%20concerned%20to%20file%20affidavits%20explaining%20their%20response%20while%20adding%20that%20it%20may%20even%20possibly%20ask%20the%20state%20police%20chief%20to%20take%20those%20charged%20with%20contempt%20of%20court%20into%20custody%20and%20to%20prison.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Surat%20police%20commissioner%20Ajay%20Kumar%20Tomar%20told%20%3Cem%3EIE%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20he%20was%20unaware%20of%20the%20incident%20and%20would%20get%20the%20matter%20checked%20from%20his%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShah%E2%80%99s%20advocate%20Syed%20accused%20Surat%20Police%20of%20being%20%E2%80%9Chand-in-glove%E2%80%9D%20with%20the%20complainant%20of%20the%20case.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20our%20plea%20before%20the%20SC%2C%20we%20have%20mentioned%20that%20the%20Surat%20police%20worked%20hand-in-glove%20with%20the%20complainant%20and%20arrested%20Shah.%20Following%20the%20police%20remand%2C%20he%20was%20again%20produced%20before%20the%20same%20judge%20%E2%80%93%206th%20Additional%20Chief%20Judicial%20Magistrate%20D.%20S.%20Thakar%20%E2%80%93%20who%20again%20denied%20our%20plea.%20We%20filed%20a%20fresh%20bail%20application%20and%20later%20Shah%20was%20released%2C%E2%80%9D%20added%20Syed.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20also%20wrote%20to%20Commissioner%20Ajay%20Kumar%20Tomar%20about%20the%20Vesu%20police%20working%20hand-in-glove%20with%20the%20complainant.%20Further%2C%20we%20filed%20an%20application%20with%20the%20Surat%20court%20but%20it%20was%20rejected.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20apex%20court%20issued%20notices%20to%C2%A0Gujarat%E2%80%99s%20a